Task 2: Real-time Collaborative Tool (Google Docs-like)
Objective

Develop a collaborative note-taking/coding platform with real-time updates using WebSockets.

Implementation

Technology stack: Node.js, Express.js, Socket.IO, Vanilla JS frontend.

Features implemented:

Multi-user support with room-based collaboration.

Real-time synchronization of text edits.

Debouncing keystrokes to reduce network traffic.

Broadcasting updates only to users in the same room.

Project structure improvements:

Separated server.js and sockets.js.

Utility functions for logging and debouncing.

Public folder for frontend (HTML, CSS, JS).

Impact

Reduced network overhead with debouncing.

Increased readability & maintainability through modular structure.

Enabled scalability for future integration with CRDT or persistent storage.
